DISCLAIMER — LIMITATION OF LIABILITY FOR CALCULATIONS

This software produces estimates based on simplified mathematical models
(pvlib solar position, Perez irradiance, NOCT thermal model, geometric
ray-casting) and third-party open source libraries. The results — including
but not limited to solar irradiance, energy production, shadow analysis,
electrical string sizing, inverter compatibility, and economic analysis —
are approximations and NOT certified engineering calculations.

The authors and contributors:
(a) Make NO warranty regarding the accuracy, completeness, or reliability
    of any calculation or simulation output;
(b) Accept NO liability for direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential
    damages arising from the use of these results for the design,
    installation, evaluation, or operation of real photovoltaic systems;
(c) Accept NO liability for errors or inaccuracies in third-party libraries
    (pvlib, trimesh, scipy, embreex, reportlab, etc.) on which this
    software depends.

Users MUST verify all results with a qualified professional engineer before
making any design, installation, or financial decision based on this
software's output.
